## Understanding
The user wants to build a password strength checker tool that evaluates password quality without storing or transmitting the password. The tool should be client-side only, with all processing done locally in the browser.

## Solution
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Password Strength Checker</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      padding: 2rem;
      background-color: #f4f4f4;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 500px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      background: white;
      padding: 2rem;
      border-radius: 8px;
      box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    }
    label {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    input[type="password"] {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 0.75rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      border: 1px solid #ccc;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }
    .strength-meter {
      height: 20px;
      background: #ddd;
      border-radius: 10px;
      overflow: hidden;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .strength-bar {
      height: 100%;
      width: 0;
      transition: width 0.3s ease;
    }
    .strength-label {
      font-weight: bold;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .strength-label.low { color: red; }
    .strength-label.medium { color: orange; }
    .strength-label.high { color: green; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Password Strength Checker</h2>
    <label for="password">Enter Password:</label>
    <input type="password" id="password" oninput="checkPasswordStrength()" />

    <div class="strength-meter">
      <div class="strength-bar" id="strengthBar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="strength-label" id="strengthLabel">Enter a password to check</div>
  </div>

  <script>
    function checkPasswordStrength() {
      const password = document.getElementById('password').value;
      const strengthBar = document.getElementById('strengthBar');
      const strengthLabel = document.getElementById('strengthLabel');

      let strength = 0;

      // Check length
      if (password.length >= 8) strength += 25;
      if (password.length >= 12) strength += 25;

      // Check for uppercase
      if (/[A-Z]/.test(password)) strength += 20;

      // Check for lowercase
      if (/[a-z]/.test(password)) strength += 20;

      // Check for numbers
      if (/\d/.test(password)) strength += 15;

      // Check for special characters
      if (/[^A-Za-z0-9]/.test(password)) strength += 15;

      // Update the bar and label
      strengthBar.style.width = strength + '%';
      strengthBar.style.backgroundColor = 
        strength < 30 ? 'red' : 
        strength < 60 ? 'orange' : 
        'green';

      strengthLabel.textContent = 
        strength < 30 ? 'Weak' : 
        strength < 60 ? 'Medium' : 
        'Strong';
      strengthLabel.className = 'strength-label ' + 
        (strength < 30 ? 'low' : 
         strength < 60 ? 'medium' : 
         'high');
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

## Quality Notes
- The solution is fully client-side, ensuring no password data is transmitted or stored.
- It uses basic JavaScript to evaluate password strength based on common criteria (length, uppercase, lowercase, numbers, special characters).
- The UI provides immediate visual feedback through a strength meter and label.
- The code is self-contained and ready to use without any external dependencies.

